<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="465" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1870,2003]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1870,1895]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. In the group VIII key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Borgmeier" box="[642,846,1870,1895]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" refString="Borgmeier, T. (1966) Revision of the North American phorid flies. Part III. The species of the genus Megaselia, subgenus Megaselia. Studia Entomologica, 8, 1 - 160." type="journal article" year="1966">
Borgmeier (
<number box="[779,839,1870,1895]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" value="1966.0">1966</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, keys to 
<taxonomicName box="[950,1135,1870,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaeoides">
<emphasis box="[950,1135,1870,1894]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">M. pygmaeoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[now considered to be 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmitz 1919" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1919" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="berndseni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">M. berndseni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schmitz" box="[278,441,1906,1931]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" refString="Schmitz, H. (1919) Neue europaeische Aphiochaeta-Arten. II. Entomologische Berichten, Ver. 5, 110 - 119." type="journal article" year="1919">
Schmitz 
<number box="[381,441,1907,1931]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" value="1919.0">1919</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
] which has a shorter costa (CI 0.30–0.33 compared to 
<taxonomicName box="[1085,1278,1907,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lombardorum">
<emphasis box="[1085,1278,1907,1931]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">M. lombardorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at 0.33–0.37, usually being at the upper end of that range) than this new species and more than twice as many spinuli on the labellum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
